            <bio>
               <p>
                  <bold>Sélim Smaoui</bold>is currently a doctoral candidate in political science at Sciences Po Paris and a visiting lecturer and research assistant at Sciences Po Aix-en-Provence. He works primarily on protest movements concerned with the victims of Franco's regime in Spain. He is also the author of works on protest movements in Morocco, and his publications include: (with Mohamed Wazif) “Étendard de lutte ou pavillon de complaisance? S'engager sous la bannière du ‘mouvement du 20 février' à Casablanca”, in Amin Allal, Thomas Pierret (eds),<italic>Au coeur des révoltes arabes. Devenir révolutionnaires</italic>(Paris: Armand Colin, 2013), 55-79 (Sciences Po Paris, CERI, 56 rue Jacob, 75006 Paris, &lt;<email xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
                         xlink:href="selims86@hotmail.com">selims86@hotmail.com</email>&gt;).</p>
            </bio>
